description: Churning under the twisted streets and elaborate architecture of Washington DC is a dark force: The Thrum. Will the whole affair become a coming out party from hell? Based on the hit Namco game named one of the Thirty must-have for the iPhone and iPod touch. description: "Night and Fog" takes place on an island where the inhabitants have been changed into monsters who evolve to survive otherwise-mortal injuries, becoming increasingly vicious with each adaptation. "It's very much in the vein of the classic '80s John Carpenter films, particularly 'The Fog' and 'The Thing.

Issue 5 (of 5) Linked to a secret from the past, an experiment in a black-ops bioengineering facility leads to a horrible freak accident. The ensuing disaster turns the inhabitants of a nearby village into a horde of rampaging creatures, leaving only a handful of survivors to escape infection. But things become dramatically worse when the survivors discover that the transformation is only one of many - into something far more horrific and unstoppable.

Everybody who enrolls at the Okinawa Actors School has big dreams: They're all hoping to sing and dance their way to the top of the Hit Parade.

But show business is a fickle business as Airi Ishikawa is quickly finding out. Fresh off a big and successful Boom Boom concert, she discovers that her friends -- and not her -- will be given an opportunity to pursue solo careers. Frustrated and dejected, she considers dropping out of school.

There's no doubt Airi's got all the talent in the world. The question remains, however: Does she have the inner strength needed to bounce back from the occasional, yet inevitable, setback?

description:
Conventional pet wisdom says that there are cat lovers and there are dog lovers-and never the two shall meet. But if there's one thing the two sides do agree on, it's that they love Patrick McDonnell's charming strip, Mutts.

Mutts has won the devotion of animal lovers and comics readers across the land. Fans love the charming humor the talented McDonnell provides, as well as his one-of-a-kind artistic style that stands apart on the funny pages. Yesh! features Earl the dog, his pal Mooch the cat, and the plethora of other lovable animal regulars who pop in and out of their lives.

Few people could conceive what animals are truly thinking until McDonnell gave us the antics and adventures of Earl and Mooch. In one series of strips, Earl reveals what pets think when their owners are late arriving home: "I must ration my dinner...who knows how long it will need to last?...The day?...The week?...The next two minutes?" His buddy Mooch declares after becoming stranded on top of a tree: "I need to reassess my goals."

The delightful personalities of McDonnell's animal stars have won the hearts and acclaim of readers the world over. Veteran cartoonist Charles Schulz called Mutts one of the best strips ever. The strip earned the National Cartoonists Society's Comic Strip of the Year Award in 1996. In 1998, McDonnell captured the Swedish Academy of Comic Art's Award for Best International Comic Strip Artist. Yesh! celebrates the subtle humor and unparalleled style of a strip that hearkens back to the classic strips of yesteryear.
name: Yesh!

description: When BEN GRIMM left earth on an experimental space mission, he had no idea he would return to a COMPLETELY DIFFERENT life. He and the rest of the crew are exposed to COSMIC RAYS that result in MUTAGENIC CHANGES. Reed Richards becomes the elastic MR. FANTASTIC, Sue Storm is THE INVISIBLE WOMAN, Johnny Storm is THE HUMAN TORCH, and Ben transforms into a hideous rock creature dubbed the thing. what will happen to ben and the rest of THE FANTASTIC FOUR as they struggle with their NEW IDENTITIES? Will these newfound SUPERHEROES be able to foil doctor doom's EVIL PLOT?

description:
You an' Me, Lord. You an' me.

"An' so I set out into what was left o' the world, intent on doin', the Lord's work. On a different journey now, but... still just a pilgrim."

-- Pilgrim

In the days before the "Burn" - when the sun scorched the Earth and evaporated the seas - the Pilgrim was a soldier who lost his way and lost his connection to humanity, becoming a depraved thing... until he found the Lord and his new purpose upon the new Earth.

Feauting the dark humor associated with Ennis' most infamous work, Just a Pilgrim is collected here in one volume for the first time. Return to Ennis' hopeless, yet fascinating, post apocalyptic world brilliantly illustrated by artist Carlos Ezquerra!

Featuring both the original mini-series and the sequel ("Garden of Eden") mini-series together in one hardcover collection, this volume also contains a complete cover gallery featuring the work of Tim Bradstreet, JG Jones, Glenn Fabry, and many more!

Introduction by Mark Waid.
